For the impatient:

    Install PyBOMBS as per the previous section

    Apply a configuration:

     $ pybombs auto-config

    Add a list of recipes, e.g., the default recipes:

     $ pybombs recipes add-defaults

    Install GNU Radio, gr-osmosdr and some other goodies into your home directory ~/prefix:

     $ pybombs prefix init ~/prefix -a myprefix -R gnuradio-default

    All commands after this will use myprefix as the default prefix. You can change the default prefix later by running pybombs config default_prefix NEWPREFIX

    Run GNU Radio Companion from your new prefix:

     $ source ~/prefix/setup_env.sh
     $ gnuradio-companion

    or execute it without changing the current environment:

     $ pybombs run gnuradio-companion


